<keyStep id="4003E798FFA5FF82FF62FB6DFA4C9CA1" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">
<paragraph id="FB48FF3DFFA5FF82FF62FB6DFA4C9C66" blockId="11.[151,1436,796,1052]" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">
<keyLead id="40065C08FFA5FF82FF62FB6DFA4C9C66" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">
1(0) Body asymmetrical; dorsal macroducts scattered; with 2 marginal gland spines lateral to L 
<subScript id="6773FD78FFA5FF82FBB0FB5AFB9C9C1F" attach="left" box="[1093,1100,811,823]" fontSize="5" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">2</subScript>
(on abd. VII) on either side................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="3CF784BEFFA5FF82FAB6FB48FA4C9C66" baseAuthorityName="Maskell" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[1347,1436,825,846]" class="Insecta" family="Diaspididae" genus="Unachionaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="531" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenuis">
<emphasis id="C983232FFFA5FF82FAB6FB48FA4C9C66" bold="true" box="[1347,1436,825,846]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">U. tenuis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FB48FF3DFFA5FF82FF62FB26FA4C9CA1" blockId="11.[151,1436,796,1052]" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">
<keyLead id="40065C08FFA5FF82FF62FB26FA4C9CA1" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">- Body symmetrical; dorsal macroducts forming segmental groups; with 1 marginal gland spine lateral to L2 (on abd. VII) on either side........................................................................................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="4003E798FFA5FF82FF62FBE0FA4C9CEB" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">
<paragraph id="FB48FF3DFFA5FF82FF62FBE0FA4C9C8E" blockId="11.[151,1436,796,1052]" box="[151,1436,912,935]" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">
<keyLead id="40065C08FFA5FF82FF62FBE0FA4C9C8E" box="[151,1436,912,935]" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">
2(1) Body widest at abd. II; metathorax and abd. I with submarginal dorsal macroducts........................ 
<taxonomicName id="3CF784BEFFA5FF82FAEEFBE0FA4C9C8E" baseAuthorityName="Cockerell" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[1307,1436,912,934]" class="Insecta" family="Diaspididae" genus="Unachionaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="531" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bambusae">
<emphasis id="C983232FFFA5FF82FAEEFBE0FA4C9C8E" bold="true" box="[1307,1436,912,934]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">U. bambusae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FB48FF3DFFA5FF82FF62FBDEFA4C9CEB" blockId="11.[151,1436,796,1052]" box="[151,1436,942,964]" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">
<keyLead id="40065C08FFA5FF82FF62FBDEFA4C9CEB" box="[151,1436,942,964]" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">- Body widest at metathorax; metathorax and abd. I without submarginal dorsal macroducts........................... 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="4003E798FFA5FF82FF62FBBDFA4C9B33" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">
<paragraph id="FB48FF3DFFA5FF82FF62FBBDFA4C9CC8" blockId="11.[151,1436,796,1052]" box="[151,1436,971,994]" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">
<keyLead id="40065C08FFA5FF82FF62FBBDFA4C9CC8" box="[151,1436,971,994]" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">
3(2) Posterior spiracle associated with trilocular pores; mesothorax and metathorax with submarginal gland spines..... 
<taxonomicName id="3CF784BEFFA5FF82FAC2FBBDFA4C9CC8" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Maskell" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[1335,1436,971,993]" class="Insecta" family="Diaspididae" genus="Unachionaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="531" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signata">
<emphasis id="C983232FFFA5FF82FAC2FBBDFA4C9CC8" bold="true" box="[1335,1436,971,993]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">U. signata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FB48FF3DFFA5FF82FF62FB98FA4C9B33" blockId="11.[151,1436,796,1052]" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">
<keyLead id="40065C08FFA5FF82FF62FB98FA4C9B33" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">
- Posterior spiracle not associated with trilocular pores; mesothorax and metathorax without submarginal gland spines..................................................................................... 
